==English==

===Etymology===
The word "toxin" comes from the Greek "toxikon" which means "arrow poison".

===Noun===
'''toxin'''

# A [[toxic]] or [[poisonous]] substance.
# A [[colloid]]al poisonous substance that is a specific product of the metabolic activities of a living organism, and is notably toxic when introduced into living tissue.

